【9】 Pharmacologic Category
【10】 *   Vitamin, Fat Soluble
【11】 Dosing: Adult
【12】 Skin protectant
【13】 **Skin protectant:** **Topical:** Apply a thin layer over affected area as needed (usually 1 to 2 times daily).
【14】 Dosing: Kidney Impairment: Adult
【15】 There are no dosage adjustments provided in the manufacturer's labeling.
【16】 Dosing: Hepatic Impairment: Adult
【17】 There are no dosage adjustments provided in the manufacturer's labeling.
【18】 Dosing: Older Adult
【19】 Refer to adult dosing.
【20】 Dosing: Pediatric
【21】 (For additional information see "Vitamin E (topical): Pediatric drug information")
【22】 Superficial dermatologic irritation
【23】 **Superficial dermatologic irritation:** Infants, Children, and Adolescents: Topical: Apply a thin layer over affected area
【24】 Adverse Reactions
【25】 There are no adverse reactions listed in the manufacturer’s labeling.
【26】 Dosage Forms: US
【27】 Excipient information presented when available (limited, particularly for generics); consult specific product labeling. \[DSC\] = Discontinued product
【28】 Cream, External:
【29】 Gordons-Vite E: 1500 units/30 g (15 g, 75 g, 480 g, 2400 g)
【30】 Gel, External:
【31】 Natural Vitamin E Moisturizing: (237 mL) \[contains methylparaben, polyethylene glycol (macrogol)\]
【32】 Liquid, External:
【33】 Generic: 920 units/mL (28.5 mL, 57 mL, 114 mL)
【34】 Lotion, External:
【35】 Vitec: (113 g \[DSC\])
【36】 Oil, External:
【37】 Vitamin E Beauty: 24,000 units/52 mL (52 mL); 49,000 units/52 mL (52 mL)
【38】 Generic: 28,000 units (29.5 mL)
【39】 Generic Equivalent Available: US
【40】 May be product dependent
【41】 Administration: Adult
【42】 **Topical:** For external use only; avoid contact with eyes. Apply to clean, dry area; rub in well. Do not apply to broken or irritated skin or areas affected by rashes.
【43】 Administration: Pediatric
【44】 Topical: For topical use only. Wash hands prior to use; apply to clean, affected area; rub in well.
【45】 Use: Labeled Indications
【46】 **Skin protectant:** Aids in the healing of scar and surgical-wound tissue; aids in moisturizing and healing skin; counteracts premature aging; reduces the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles.
【47】 Metabolism/Transport Effects
【48】 None known.
【49】 Drug Interactions  
【50】   
【51】 (For additional information: Launch drug interactions program)
【52】 There are no known significant interactions.
【53】 Mechanism of Action
【54】 Prevents oxidation of vitamin A and C; protects polyunsaturated fatty acids in membranes from attack by free radicals and protects red blood cells against hemolysis
